olor either look back at\n# a previous project or google "Python turtle color".\ncolor = input("Please enter a color")\nt.color(color)\n# TODO: Ask the user how big they would like a square,\n# then draw a square that size. Remember that input()\n# gives a string, so you"ll need to convert the string\n# to an integer, like what we did with the numbers earlier\n# in the program.\nsize = int(input("How big would you like the square?"))\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\n# TODO: Draw a square twice the size of the previous one.\n# You"ll do this by modifying the variable representing\n# the size. Do NOT ask the user for a new size.\nsize = size * 2\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\nt.forward(size)\nt.left(90)\n# TODO: Ask the user for something interesting and do\n# something interesting with it. Remember that you may not\n# use if statements or loops.\n','module_id' => $module3->id,'previous_lesson_id' => $lesson4->id,'user_id' => $user->id]);
