$project7 = Project::create(['name' => ' Darts','open_date' => '2018-06-23 0:00:00','close_date' => '2018-06-25 0:00:00','prompt' => '\n<div>You will be implementing the first iteration of a dart throwing program. Your program should behave similarly to what is shown in <a href="https://youtu.be/6F4pW4cDx44" target="_blank">this video</a>.\nThe starter code sets the shape of your turtle. When the dart moves toward the target it is actually the turtle moving. You will control the speed of the turtle with the t.speed() function.\nOther functions you will want to use include:\n<ul>\n<li>t.dot(d, "red") -- draws a circle of diameter d filled in red</li>\n<li>t.setpos(x, y) -- moves the turtle to position (x, y)</li>\n<li>random.randint(-100, 100) -- gives a random number between -100 and 100</li>\n<li>t.hideturtle() -- makes the turtle invisible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You must have at least one function called throw(). You may have other functions as well.\n<p>Use meaningful variable names, such as numRings and numThrows.\n<p>This project is to be done individually.\n</div>\n','pre_code' => '','start_code' => 'import turtle\nimport random\nt = turtle.Turtle()\nscreen = turtle.Screen()\nscreen.addshape("dart", ((-2,-2), (2,-2), (2,2), (-2,2)))\nt.shape("dart")\nt.fillcolor("green")\nt.color("green")\n','solution' => 'import turtle\nimport random\nt = turtle.Turtle()\nscreen = turtle.Screen()\nscreen.addshape("dart", ((-2,-2), (2,-2), (2,2), (-2,2)))\nt.shape("dart")\nt.fillcolor("green")\nt.color("green")\nnumRings = int(input("Number of rings:"))\nnumThrows = int(input("Number of throws:"))\ninc = int(100/numRings)\nfor i in range(100, 0, -inc*2):\n    t.dot(i, "red")\n    t.dot(i-inc, "blue")\nfor i in range(0, numThrows):\n    t.up()\n    t.speed(10000)\n    t.setpos(100, 100)\n    t.left(180)\n    t.speed(1)\n    x = random.randint(-100, 100)\n    y = random.randint(-100, 100)\n    t.setpos(x, y)\n    t.dot(4, "green")\nt.hideturtle()\n','module_id' => $module7->id,'previous_lesson_id' => $lesson14->id,'user_id' => $user->id]);
